# Template-net10 — Cursor rules

This repository is a fully documented .NET 10 starter kit. **The documentation is the source of
truth. Read it before writing code, and keep it up to date.**

## Read first (required, in order)

1. **`AGENTS.md`** — primary operating guide: architecture, conventions, golden rules, recipes.
   Authoritative; if anything conflicts, `AGENTS.md` wins.
2. **`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`** — long-form architecture reference.
3. **`docs-site/content/**`** — per-feature usage docs (auth, authorization, caching, storage,
   encryption, hashing, excel, pdf, realtime/websockets, idempotency, helpers, docker, …).

## Non-negotiable rules

- Obey every convention and **Golden rule** in `AGENTS.md`. Search `docs-site/content/**` and `docs/`
  before inventing a pattern.
- Match existing code: Clean Architecture + CQRS + MediatR; feature-organized folders; namespace ==
  folder path.
- When you add or change a feature, **update the docs**: `docs-site/content/**` (+
  `docs-site/src/lib/navigation.ts`), and `AGENTS.md` / `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` if conventions change.
- A task is done only when `dotnet build Template-net10.slnx` is green (0 errors) and
  `dotnet test Tests/Template-net10.UnitTests/...` passes.
- Do not introduce forbidden patterns: Repository pattern, business logic in handlers/controllers,
  hardcoded user-facing strings, multi-tenancy, or hand-authored EF migrations.

Treat `AGENTS.md` as the canonical rule set; this file only points you to it.
